item.title: Boris Johnson warns Covid risk remains as he unveils England's winter plan
item.description: But he says the UK is better placed to tackle the disease as he outlines England's winter plan.

item.title: Notting Hill crash: Three dead after car hits block of flats and catches fire
item.description: Three people die after a car crashes into a block of flats and bursts into flames in Notting Hill.

item.title: Grimsby hospital: High demand blamed for A&E queue
item.description: There was a lack of space for walk-ins at Grimsby's hospital due to social distancing, a trust says.

item.title: Buckland St Mary air crash: Family pays tribute to killed artist
item.description: Margaret Costa, who died in an air crash was her family's "foundation stone", her relatives say.

item.title: Tributes to RAF instructor after parachute jump death
item.description: Sgt Rachel Fisk died while taking part in a free-fall parachute jump at RAF Weston-on-the-Green.

item.title: Bradford Toller Lane crash: CCTV footage shown at inquest
item.description: The BMW was travelling at 65mph when it hit a tree in Bradford, a fatal crash inquest hears.

item.title: Matfen Hall: Couples 'distraught' as weddings cancelled amid price hike
item.description: Couples due to wed at a country hotel are told they must spend Â£20,000 or lose their bookings.

item.title: Brendon Prince: Paddleboarder finishes 3,800-mile challenge
item.description: Sea safety campaigner Brendon Prince circumnavigates mainland Britain by paddleboard.

item.title: Cawston Park: Police re-examine Joanna Bailey case
item.description: Norfolk Police is to look again at the death of Joanna Bailey at the now-closed Cawston Park.

item.title: Nicholas Burton: 'Merciless' killer due to be released
item.description: Nicholas Burton was found guilty of stabbing 27-year-old Rachel McGrath to death in 1997.

item.title: Hinckley football team make history in 18-0 FA Vase win
item.description: Nine different players scored to help the club achieve its biggest margin of victory.

item.title: Thin Blue Paw Awards: Suicide-prevention dog wins
item.description: German shepherd Calli and PC Megan West win the lifesaver category at the Thin Blue Paw Awards.

item.title: The litter-laden alleyways transformed by residents
item.description: Residents decided to turn fly-tipping-laden alleyways into vibrant community spaces.

item.title: Coronavirus: Matlock Bath Illuminations return after cancellation
item.description: The colourful event in Derbyshire sees hand-crafted boats parade along the River Derwent.

item.title: Suffolk school visited by Wattisham Airfield Apache helicopter
item.description: Pupils at Kersey Primary School are given a show and tell they will never forget.

item.title: Felixstowe arrival of largest container ship Ever Ace caught on drone
item.description: The aerial pictures show the Ever Ace coming in to dock at Felixstowe in Suffolk.

item.title: M25 climate protest: Aerials show long traffic queues as junctions blocked
item.description: Climate change protesters are demanding government action on home insulation.

item.title: Oxford taxi driver jailed for raping passenger
item.description: Asif Khan attacked the woman after collecting her from Oxford's Atik nightclub.

item.title: Snowdon: Man crawls for seven hours to reach summit
item.description: Paul Smith, who has used a wheelchair for 30 years, said the challenge was an "emotional" experience.

item.title: Driver jailed for crash that killed teen passenger
item.description: Fahren Smith was behind the wheel of a car which had five passengers inside when it crashed.

item.title: Steve Jagielka: Ex-Shrewsbury Town star's death was drug related
item.description: Steve Jagielka played more than 170 times for Shrewsbury Town between 1997 and 2003.

item.title: M25 protests: Arrest tally over Insulate Britain action reaches 77
item.description: Police thank drivers for their "patience and understanding" during the disruption.

item.title: Emma Raducanu celebrated with Royal Mail postmark
item.description: The postmark congratulates the US Open Champion for "A First Class performance".

item.title: Young Boys 2-1 Manchester United: Cristiano Ronaldo scores but Red Devils suffer shock defeat
item.description: Cristiano Ronaldo scores on his Champions League return for Manchester United but it is not enough as Young Boys strike in stoppage-time to cap a remarkable comeback win.

item.title: County Championship: Hampshire beat Nottinghamshire to lead title race
item.description: Hampshire will lead the title race into the final round of Championship games after a 122-run win over Nottinghamshire.

item.title: Michael Shenton: Castleford Tigers captain to retire at 35 at end of 2021 season
item.description: Castleford Tigers captain Michael Shenton is to retire at the end of the 2021 Super League campaign, after 18 seasons.
